<DESCRIPT>  HOLIDAY; FLOWER; GUIDELINE  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  EXOTIC tropicals symbolize the '80s; backyard blooms, the '90s. Color is more
important today than flower type, but to avoid embarrassment remember that red
roses still signify love and gladioli, funerals, to a lot of people.;   Here
are a few other tips for creating your own bouquets:  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Special Section  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  TIPS HELP BACKYARD BLOOMS LAST  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Holiday Homes: A Special Section; See also related article on this page.  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     (check) Go for the greenery first. Leaves, ferns or whatever should be
anchored before adding flowers around them to build a set arrangement. For a
casual bouquet, tie a string around stems before putting flowers in the vase.;
  (check) Flowers that spring from bulbs -- tulips, lilies, iris -- appreciate
a cold shower, but all others prefer a bath of warm water once they're in the
vase.;   (check) Avoid yucky stems and greenish water by adding a tablespoon
of bleach at the start.;   (check) Professionals use a solution of silver
nitrate to make roses last a week to 10 days.  </TEXT>
